-- Actelion, Deutsche Telekom, Renault: Europe Equity Preview
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-01-10T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/actelion-deutsche-telekom-renault-europe-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European (SXXP)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  fell 0.5 percent to 246.42. The
 Stoxx 50 Index  declined 0.6 percent to 2,385.73. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro,
retreated 0.5 percent to 2,286.45.  Actelion Ltd. (ATLN)  (ATLN VX): The Swiss maker of the Tracleer
lung drug said it will miss its 2011 profit-growth forecast and
repeated that sales this year will fall as it faces increased
pricing and competitive pressure. The shares fell 0.2 percent to
33.44 francs.  Deutsche Telekom AG (DTE)  (DTE GY):  Europe ’s biggest phone
company will develop a new strategy for T-Mobile USA Inc. in the
upcoming weeks following the withdrawal of AT&T Inc.’s bid,
Reuters reported, citing a person familiar with the matter.
Deutsche Telekom fell 0.6 percent to 8.8 euros.  Renault SA (RNO)  :  Carlos Ghosn , chief executive officer
of the French automaker and Nissan Motor Co. said the two
affiliates may be weeks away from an agreement to buy control of
 Russia ’s biggest carmaker, OAO AvtoVAZ. Renault fell 0.4 percent
to 28.20 euros.  STMicroelectronics NV (STM)  : Europe’s largest
semiconductor maker will unveil a smart-suit prototype with
motion sensors that may help people with injuries to recover
faster and enhance the performance of athletes. The shares fell
0.7 percent to 4.82 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
